# Environment Variables

Copy this file to `.env` and fill in your API keys.

```bash
cp .env.example .env
```

## Required API Keys

Set these only for the providers you plan to use:

```bash
# Gemini (research, editing, final review)
GEMINI_API_KEY=

# Groq (routing, checks, metadata)
GROQ_API_KEY=

# Qwen / DashScope (outlines, drafting, technical)
QWEN_API_KEY=

# Ollama (local) — no key needed if running locally
OLLAMA_BASE_URL=http://localhost:11434

# Optional: only for hosted Ollama-compatible endpoints that require auth
OLLAMA_API_KEY=

# Server port (optional, default 3030)
PORT=3030

# Lead discovery providers (optional)
SERPAPI_KEY=
APIFY_TOKEN=
APIFY_ACTOR_ID=
OUTSCRAPER_API_KEY=
YOUTUBE_API_KEY=
```

## Provider Quick Reference

| Agent | Default Provider | When to Use |
|---|---|---|
| Router | Groq | Fast routing decisions |
| Research | Gemini Pro | Long context, web research |
| Outline | Qwen | Structured outlines |
| Draft | Qwen Coder | First drafts |
| Editor | Gemini Pro | Clarity and flow |
| Checker | Groq | Fast checklist validation |
| Final Reviewer | Gemini Pro | Quality gate |
| Metadata | Groq | Fast metadata generation |
| Publisher | Qwen | Publishing package |
